  <sections xmi:id="_Z9r9wP87EduLr5zGs322wA" name="Create Asset Rules and Policies" guid="_Z9r9wP87EduLr5zGs322wA">
    <sectionDescription>&lt;p>&#xD;
    Identify the categories of asset rules that need to be created, such as Asset Type Rules, and so forth. Define the&#xD;
    version of the particular set of rules. Describe the rules and policies. Describe the target audience for complying&#xD;
    with the rule.&#xD;
&lt;/p></sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_cA0TIP87EduLr5zGs322wA" name="Review the Asset Rules and Policies with the Users" guid="_cA0TIP87EduLr5zGs322wA">
    <sectionDescription>The key here is to achieve buy-in and support from the teams that will be using and impacted by the rules: the asset&#xD;
manufacturing and usage teams.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
  <sections xmi:id="_gk4UMP87EduLr5zGs322wA" name="Share the Asset Rules and Policies with the Repository Administrators" guid="_gk4UMP87EduLr5zGs322wA">
    <sectionDescription>The administrators will configure the asset repository to comply with the rules.</sectionDescription>
  </sections>
